<h4>Product details</h4>
<p>Use this space for concrete fit, fabric, lining, stretch, closure, length, and care information. Keep the copy specific to the product so shoppers can compare styles with confidence.</p>
<h4>Styling and care notes</h4>
<div class="overflow-hidden"><img src="//cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0026/2956/6516/files/09_135c04ce-0c74-489e-9660-a4dc239c84c5_large.png?v=1538408527" alt="" class="mr-30 mb-25" width="470" height="343" style="float: left;" />
    <p>Describe when the item works best, how the silhouette fits, and what layers or shoes pair well with it. Mention whether the piece is fitted, relaxed, structured, lightweight, lined, or stretch-backed only when accurate.</p>
    <p><em>Care instructions should match the garment label or product data. Avoid unsupported fabric or luxury claims.</em></p>
</div>
<div class="overflow-hidden"><img src="//cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0026/2956/6516/files/10_77ecb486-c28c-49b6-929f-170a4bf0f496_large.png?v=1538409807" alt="" class="ml-30 mb-25" width="270" height="197" style="float: right;" />
    <p>Use product photos and variant notes to support the written copy. If the fabric, lining, or trim is not confirmed, say that details are shown in the product photos instead of inventing material claims.</p>
</div>
<div class="overflow-hidden">
    <div class="row">
